4. A tool according to claim 1, wherein said shank comprises:
a smaller-diameter portion on which said cutting blade is mounted;
a larger-diameter portion mounted on a tool holder; and
a tapered portion disposed between said smaller-diameter portion and said larger-diameter portion;
wherein said sub-inlet holes are open at said tapered portion and are equally angularly spaced in a circumferential direction of said shank.
